name: Fat Boy Nacho Cheese Dip
author: JULIECT
summary: My husband named this dish.  A wonderfully cheesy dip with spiced ground sausage and green chiles.  Served warm with corn chips, it always goes so fast at parties.  If you are lucky enough to have leftovers, it makes great breakfast burritos the next day.
ingredients: 1 (2 pound) loaf processed cheese food, cubed
1 (10.75 ounce) can  condensed nacho cheese soup
1 (4 ounce) can diced green chile peppers, drained
directions: Place processed cheese into a slow cooker and set to Low
Meanwhile, cook sausage in a large skillet over medium-high heat until evenly browned
Stir frequently and break into small crumbles
Drain the grease, and stir into the cheese in the slow cooker
Mix in the cheese soup and green chilies
Keep warm in the slow cooker, and serve with tortilla chips
